WEBVTT

00:00:16.917 --> 00:00:18.667
"In 2022, mankind finally"

00:00:21.625 --> 00:00:23.583
"built a full virtual environment"

00:00:29.792 --> 00:00:33.375
<i>All right, we're under way!</i>
<i>It's time for this week's MMO Stream.</i>

00:00:33.375 --> 00:00:35.458
<i>First, we had you watch</i>
<i>a promotional video...</i>

00:00:35.458 --> 00:00:37.083
<i>Are we looking at the day</i>
<i>of last week's launch?</i>

00:00:37.083 --> 00:00:37.792
"End of Line"
<i>Are we looking at the day of last week's launch?</i>

00:00:37.792 --> 00:00:40.042
"End of Line"
<i>What could all these people waiting in line be after?</i>

00:00:40.250 --> 00:00:41.917
<i>Sword Art Online!</i>

00:00:42.208 --> 00:00:44.458
<i>The one at the front of the line waited</i>
<i>for three days prior to launch.</i>

00:00:44.458 --> 00:00:45.792
<i>Amazing!</i>

00:00:45.792 --> 00:00:47.417
<i> </i>
<i>  </i>
<i>Or is this just what any real gamer would do?</i>

00:00:47.417 --> 00:00:48.625
"Sword Art Online
Development Director Akihiko Kayaba"
<i>Or is this just what any real gamer would do?</i>

00:00:48.625 --> 00:00:51.917
<i>On today's MMO Stream,</i>
<i>we'll be covering</i>

00:00:51.917 --> 00:00:55.750
<i>the internationally famous</i>
<i>Sword Art Online, AKA SAO!</i>

00:00:55.750 --> 00:00:59.333
<i>To be honest, none of the NerveGear</i>
<i>software released so far</i>

00:00:59.333 --> 00:01:01.458
<i>has really taken advantage</i>
<i>of the hardware.</i>

00:01:01.458 --> 00:01:02.250
Big brother...

00:01:02.250 --> 00:01:03.625
<i>--Yeah, they were crappy games, huh?</i>

00:01:03.625 --> 00:01:04.208
--I'm off to practice.
<i>--Yeah, they were crappy games, huh?</i>

00:01:04.208 --> 00:01:05.542
--I'm off to practice.
<i>--But SAO was made</i>

00:01:05.542 --> 00:01:09.042
<i>by the NerveGear inventor, Akihiko Kayaba,</i>

00:01:09.042 --> 00:01:12.917
<i>and it's a long-awaited</i>
<i>VR MMORPG. I can't wait!</i>

00:01:12.917 --> 00:01:15.167
<i>The beta testers all</i>
<i>said it was incredible.</i>

00:01:15.167 --> 00:01:16.542
<i>I wish I could've</i>
<i>gotten a copy too...</i>

00:01:16.542 --> 00:01:18.292
<i>Only 10,000 copies were</i>
<i>sold in its first printing.</i>

00:01:18.292 --> 00:01:20.292
<i>It sold out online in seconds.</i>

00:01:20.292 --> 00:01:24.417
<i>And as you saw, hard-core fans</i>
<i>bought all the store copies.</i>

00:01:39.583 --> 00:01:40.750
Link start!

00:01:51.083 --> 00:01:52.875
"Character Registration
Use beta-test data?"

00:02:13.375 --> 00:02:14.583
I've come back!

00:02:15.167 --> 00:02:16.500
To this world!

00:02:38.125 --> 00:02:42.125
"The World of Swords"

00:02:42.375 --> 00:02:44.875
"Floor 1: Town of Beginnings"

00:02:44.875 --> 00:02:46.625
So like I told him...

00:02:46.625 --> 00:02:48.042
Hey, let's team up as a party.

00:02:48.042 --> 00:02:50.292
Hmm, what should I do?

00:02:50.292 --> 00:02:52.417
Oh, come on!

00:02:56.708 --> 00:02:59.708
Hey, you there! Bro!

00:03:01.958 --> 00:03:03.042
Me?

00:03:06.333 --> 00:03:08.375
You move without hesitation...

00:03:08.375 --> 00:03:10.042
Were you in the beta test?

00:03:10.042 --> 00:03:11.667
Y-Yeah.

00:03:11.667 --> 00:03:14.125
Today's my first day, see.

00:03:14.292 --> 00:03:16.708
Give me a tip to get through
the early levels, huh?

00:03:16.708 --> 00:03:18.000
U-Uh...

00:03:18.500 --> 00:03:20.375
Come on, I'm begging you!

00:03:21.083 --> 00:03:22.958
My name's Klein.
Nice to meet you.

00:03:24.792 --> 00:03:26.917
I'm Kirito.

00:03:29.958 --> 00:03:34.042
"Floor 1: Town of Beginnings, West Field"
Right in the crotch...

00:03:34.042 --> 00:03:35.833
You're so over the top.

00:03:35.833 --> 00:03:37.625
You don't feel any pain, right?

00:03:38.542 --> 00:03:39.750
Oh, yeah. That's right.

00:03:39.750 --> 00:03:40.958
Couldn't help myself!

00:03:41.333 --> 00:03:42.583
I told you.

00:03:42.583 --> 00:03:45.292
What's important is your
initial motion input.

00:03:45.292 --> 00:03:47.250
That's easy for you to say!

00:03:47.250 --> 00:03:49.375
But he keeps moving around.

00:03:50.667 --> 00:03:53.000
If you do the motion input right,

00:03:53.917 --> 00:03:56.750
and activate a sword skill,

00:04:02.958 --> 00:04:06.250
the system will ensure that
you hit your target.

00:04:06.250 --> 00:04:08.333
Motion input... Motion input...

00:04:09.667 --> 00:04:11.708
How should I put it?

00:04:13.750 --> 00:04:17.583
Add a slight pause, and when you
feel the skill begin to activate,

00:04:17.583 --> 00:04:19.375
drive it home, like "bam!"

00:04:19.792 --> 00:04:21.917
Like... "bam."

00:04:44.792 --> 00:04:47.958
All right!

00:04:48.375 --> 00:04:50.083
Congrats.

00:04:52.625 --> 00:04:53.875
However...

00:04:55.083 --> 00:04:57.833
That's as weak as slimes
in other games.

00:04:57.833 --> 00:04:59.625
Huh? Seriously?

00:04:59.625 --> 00:05:02.000
I thought it was a mid-level
boss or something.

00:05:02.625 --> 00:05:04.667
Of course not.

00:05:07.667 --> 00:05:08.958
Addictive, isn't it?

00:05:08.958 --> 00:05:10.625
Well, yeah!

00:05:12.167 --> 00:05:16.708
These skills... there are lots of them,
like forging weapons and stuff, right?

00:05:16.708 --> 00:05:17.917
I guess so.

00:05:18.167 --> 00:05:21.583
I've heard there's an
infinite variety of skills.

00:05:21.583 --> 00:05:24.250
On the other hand, there's no magic.

00:05:24.875 --> 00:05:27.083
An RPG without magic?

00:05:27.083 --> 00:05:29.875
That's a pretty bold decision.

00:05:33.750 --> 00:05:37.542
Isn't it more fun to move
your body as you fight?

00:05:38.333 --> 00:05:39.458
True that!

00:05:41.583 --> 00:05:43.625
Okay, let's move on.

00:05:43.625 --> 00:05:46.083
Yeah, let's keep going!

00:05:53.875 --> 00:05:56.875
I still can't believe it, no matter
how many times I see it...

00:05:56.875 --> 00:05:59.292
That we're in a game.

00:06:00.000 --> 00:06:02.750
Whoever made it is a genius.

00:06:03.042 --> 00:06:05.250
It really is amazing...

00:06:05.250 --> 00:06:08.167
Seriously, I'm glad I was
born in this time.

00:06:08.167 --> 00:06:10.042
You make a big deal
out of everything.

00:06:10.208 --> 00:06:12.625
Well, hey, it's my first full dive!

00:06:12.625 --> 00:06:17.167
Then this is your first time
playing a game with NerveGear?

00:06:17.167 --> 00:06:22.500
Well, it's more like I rushed out to buy
the hardware so that I could play SAO.

00:06:22.917 --> 00:06:28.000
I was really lucky to get
one of the 10,000 copies.

00:06:28.000 --> 00:06:32.583
Well, you were 10 times as lucky,
getting into the beta test.

00:06:33.167 --> 00:06:36.000
I mean, only 1,000
people got to do it.

00:06:36.167 --> 00:06:38.167
Yeah, well, I guess so.

00:06:38.167 --> 00:06:41.458
How far did you get in the beta?

00:06:41.458 --> 00:06:44.792
In a couple months,
only to floor eight.

00:06:45.333 --> 00:06:48.625
This time, one month should
be more than enough.

00:06:49.458 --> 00:06:51.792
You're really into this, huh?

00:06:51.792 --> 00:06:54.708
To be honest, during the beta test,

00:06:54.708 --> 00:06:58.500
SAO was all I thought about,
day and night.

00:06:59.667 --> 00:07:03.417
In this world, a single blade can take
you anywhere you want to go.

00:07:04.125 --> 00:07:06.500
It's a virtual world,

00:07:06.500 --> 00:07:10.625
but I still feel more alive here
than I do in the real one.

00:07:13.000 --> 00:07:16.083
Now then, want to hunt some more?

00:07:16.083 --> 00:07:17.500
Of course!

00:07:17.500 --> 00:07:19.417
I mean I'd love to,

00:07:20.208 --> 00:07:22.042
but I'm really hungry...

00:07:22.042 --> 00:07:23.292
I'm logging out.

00:07:23.292 --> 00:07:27.125
Right, eating here only
makes you feel full.

00:07:27.792 --> 00:07:30.625
I already ordered a steaming
hot pizza for 5:30 PM.

00:07:30.625 --> 00:07:32.042
You're totally prepared, aren't you?

00:07:32.042 --> 00:07:33.000
Yup!

00:07:33.000 --> 00:07:35.917
Well, once I've eaten,
I'll log back in.

00:07:36.542 --> 00:07:38.042
I see.

00:07:38.042 --> 00:07:44.125
Hey, after this, I'm meeting up with
some people I know from another game.

00:07:44.292 --> 00:07:47.667
What do you say?
Want to friend them too?

00:07:50.167 --> 00:07:53.292
Of course, I'm not forcing
you to or anything.

00:07:53.500 --> 00:07:56.083
I'm sure there'll be other
chances to introduce you.

00:07:56.083 --> 00:07:57.875
Yeah, sorry.

00:07:58.792 --> 00:07:59.750
Thanks.

00:07:59.750 --> 00:08:02.917
Hey, hey, that's my line.

00:08:02.917 --> 00:08:05.792
I'll be sure to pay you back
for this sometime...

00:08:05.792 --> 00:08:07.458
Mentally.

00:08:09.000 --> 00:08:11.083
Thanks so much, man.

00:08:12.125 --> 00:08:14.042
I'll see you around.

00:08:14.042 --> 00:08:17.208
If you have any other questions,
call me anytime.

00:08:17.208 --> 00:08:20.125
Sure! I'm counting on you!

00:08:26.375 --> 00:08:27.375
Huh?

00:08:28.708 --> 00:08:30.917
There's no button to log out.

00:08:30.917 --> 00:08:32.625
Look closer.

00:08:33.792 --> 00:08:35.500
No, I don't see it anywhere.

00:08:36.167 --> 00:08:38.667
At the bottom of the main menu...

00:08:42.667 --> 00:08:44.042
Not there, right?

00:08:44.042 --> 00:08:45.708
No, it isn't.

00:08:46.417 --> 00:08:49.708
Well, it's the first day out of beta.

00:08:49.708 --> 00:08:51.292
There must be some bugs.

00:08:51.292 --> 00:08:53.958
I'm sure the server people
are freaking out...

00:08:54.417 --> 00:08:55.833
You will be, too.

00:08:56.417 --> 00:08:58.917
It's 5:25 PM.

00:09:00.167 --> 00:09:03.167
My teriyaki-mayo pizza and ginger ale!

00:09:03.167 --> 00:09:05.750
Just hurry and call the game master.

00:09:07.458 --> 00:09:10.708
I already tried, but
nothing's happening.

00:09:10.708 --> 00:09:13.500
Was there any other
way to log out?

00:09:16.375 --> 00:09:20.042
No, if a player wants to
log themselves out,

00:09:20.042 --> 00:09:22.292
they have to go
through the menu.

00:09:22.292 --> 00:09:23.917
That's nuts.

00:09:23.917 --> 00:09:25.583
There's gotta be some way.

00:09:25.583 --> 00:09:26.708
Return!

00:09:26.708 --> 00:09:27.583
Log out!

00:09:27.583 --> 00:09:29.083
Escape!

00:09:34.667 --> 00:09:36.292
Didn't I tell you?

00:09:36.458 --> 00:09:40.042
There wasn't an emergency logout
in the manual either.

00:09:40.042 --> 00:09:42.625
Hey, you're kidding, right?

00:09:42.625 --> 00:09:43.458
I know.

00:09:43.458 --> 00:09:45.833
I'll rip the NerveGear off my head...

00:09:45.833 --> 00:09:46.917
You can't.

00:09:47.083 --> 00:09:50.542
We can't move our
real bodies right now.

00:09:50.708 --> 00:09:56.667
The NerveGear intercepts any command
issued from our brains right here.

00:09:57.500 --> 00:09:59.333
Seriously?

00:09:59.625 --> 00:10:02.667
So we have to wait for
them to fix the bug?

00:10:02.667 --> 00:10:05.500
Or for someone in the real world

00:10:05.500 --> 00:10:08.875
to remove the NerveGear from us.

00:10:08.875 --> 00:10:11.042
But I live alone.

00:10:11.042 --> 00:10:12.208
What about you?

00:10:12.542 --> 00:10:14.583
I have a mom and a little sister.

00:10:14.583 --> 00:10:17.458
So I think they'll notice
by dinner time...

00:10:18.167 --> 00:10:21.083
H-How old's your little sister, Kirito?

00:10:21.917 --> 00:10:24.292
She's on a sports team,

00:10:24.292 --> 00:10:25.792
and she hates games.

00:10:25.792 --> 00:10:27.292
She has nothing to do
with people like us.

00:10:27.292 --> 00:10:28.292
That doesn't ma--

00:10:31.667 --> 00:10:33.708
Oh wait, it doesn't hurt, right?

00:10:33.708 --> 00:10:36.417
Forget that. Don't you
find this weird?

00:10:36.417 --> 00:10:38.083
Sure, I do.

00:10:38.083 --> 00:10:39.833
It's a bug.

00:10:39.833 --> 00:10:41.833
It isn't just a bug.

00:10:41.833 --> 00:10:43.583
If we can't log out,

00:10:43.583 --> 00:10:46.625
that is a serious problem
for the game's future operation.

00:10:47.625 --> 00:10:50.000
Come to think of it, you're right.

00:10:50.000 --> 00:10:55.958
If needed, they could shut down the server
and log everyone out forcibly.

00:10:55.958 --> 00:10:58.292
But there hasn't even been
an announcement...

00:11:28.667 --> 00:11:30.250
What's going on?

00:11:30.250 --> 00:11:31.375
I don't know.

00:11:31.375 --> 00:11:33.792
A forced teleport?

00:11:41.333 --> 00:11:42.958
Up there.

00:11:47.542 --> 00:11:48.875
That's...

00:12:05.333 --> 00:12:07.625
What is that?

00:12:13.750 --> 00:12:14.833
A game master?

00:12:14.833 --> 00:12:15.875
Why doesn't he have a face?

00:12:15.875 --> 00:12:17.500
Is this an event?

00:12:17.500 --> 00:12:18.625
I'm scared...

00:12:18.625 --> 00:12:19.625
It's fine.

00:12:19.625 --> 00:12:21.917
It's just another part of
the opening ceremony.

00:12:22.708 --> 00:12:24.500
Attention, players.

00:12:25.000 --> 00:12:27.500
Welcome to my world.

00:12:27.792 --> 00:12:29.250
"My world"?

00:12:29.667 --> 00:12:32.083
My name is Akihiko Kayaba.

00:12:32.250 --> 00:12:36.500
As of this moment, I am the only
person able to control this world.

00:12:38.417 --> 00:12:39.667
Is that really him?

00:12:39.667 --> 00:12:41.292
This is really elaborate!

00:12:41.292 --> 00:12:48.125
I'm sure you've already noticed that the logout
button is missing from the main menu.

00:12:48.500 --> 00:12:51.708
But this is not a defect in the game.

00:12:52.375 --> 00:12:53.875
I repeat...

00:12:53.875 --> 00:12:55.167
This is not a defect in the game,

00:12:55.167 --> 00:12:58.833
but a key feature
of Sword Art Online.

00:12:58.833 --> 00:13:00.667
A-A feature?

00:13:00.667 --> 00:13:04.208
You cannot log out of SAO
of your own will.

00:13:04.208 --> 00:13:06.750
And no one on the outside

00:13:06.750 --> 00:13:09.833
can shut down or remove
the NerveGear.

00:13:10.167 --> 00:13:12.333
Should this be attempted,

00:13:12.333 --> 00:13:16.292
the transmitter inside the NerveGear
will emit powerful microwaves,

00:13:16.292 --> 00:13:19.792
destroying your brain and
thus ending your life.

00:13:20.042 --> 00:13:20.917
What?

00:13:20.917 --> 00:13:22.583
This must be a performance to make
the opening more exciting.

00:13:22.583 --> 00:13:23.875
Come on, enough already.

00:13:23.875 --> 00:13:25.458
Let's go.

00:13:26.542 --> 00:13:28.583
Hey, I can't get out!

00:13:29.625 --> 00:13:31.458
What's he talking about?

00:13:31.458 --> 00:13:33.375
He's gotta be nuts.

00:13:33.375 --> 00:13:34.708
Right, Kirito?

00:13:34.708 --> 00:13:38.958
He's right that the transmitter's signals
work just like microwaves.

00:13:38.958 --> 00:13:41.792
If the safety were disabled,
it could fry your brain.

00:13:41.792 --> 00:13:44.167
Then if we cut the power...

00:13:44.167 --> 00:13:47.417
No, the NerveGear has
an internal battery.

00:13:50.500 --> 00:13:51.958
But this is crazy.

00:13:51.958 --> 00:13:53.375
What's going on?

00:13:53.375 --> 00:13:58.833
Unfortunately, there have been several
instances where players' friends and families

00:13:58.833 --> 00:14:03.750
have ignored this warning, and attempted
to forcibly remove the NerveGear.

00:14:03.750 --> 00:14:07.042
As a result, 213 players

00:14:07.042 --> 00:14:11.500
have exited permanently, from both
Aincrad and the real world.

00:14:11.500 --> 00:14:13.333
Two hundred and thirteen?

00:14:13.333 --> 00:14:14.625
I don't believe it...

00:14:14.625 --> 00:14:16.375
I don't believe it!

00:14:16.375 --> 00:14:19.625
As you can see, news organizations
across the world

00:14:19.625 --> 00:14:23.375
are reporting on this situation,
including the multiple deaths.

00:14:23.375 --> 00:14:30.458
"Death Count Rises in Online-Game Incident"
Thus, you can assume that the danger of
a NerveGear being removed has been reduced.

00:14:30.458 --> 00:14:34.625
So, I would like you all to focus
on clearing the game.

00:14:36.583 --> 00:14:39.292
But be sure to keep this in mind.

00:14:39.292 --> 00:14:43.208
There is no longer any function to
revive someone within the game.

00:14:43.208 --> 00:14:48.167
The instant your HP drops to zero,
your avatars will vanish forever.

00:14:48.167 --> 00:14:49.167
And simultaneously,

00:14:50.625 --> 00:14:55.250
you brains will be destroyed
by the NerveGear.

00:15:10.542 --> 00:15:16.167
The one condition for your escape
is to complete this game.

00:15:16.667 --> 00:15:21.417
You are presently on the
lowest floor of Aincrad, floor one.

00:15:21.417 --> 00:15:23.542
If you make your way
through the dungeon

00:15:23.542 --> 00:15:26.542
and defeat the Floor Boss,
you may advance to the next level.

00:15:26.542 --> 00:15:30.458
Defeat the final boss on floor 100
and you will clear the game.

00:15:30.792 --> 00:15:31.458
Clear?

00:15:31.458 --> 00:15:32.667
What's he talking about?

00:15:33.208 --> 00:15:35.417
D-Don't just make stuff up!

00:15:35.417 --> 00:15:38.333
Clear all 100 floors?

00:15:38.625 --> 00:15:40.208
That's impossible.

00:15:40.458 --> 00:15:42.875
Even the beta testers never
made it that high, right?

00:15:44.125 --> 00:15:46.000
Now then, finally,

00:15:46.500 --> 00:15:51.083
I've provided you all with
a present in your item storage.

00:15:51.083 --> 00:15:53.125
Please see for yourselves.

00:15:56.250 --> 00:15:57.000
"Mirror"

00:15:57.000 --> 00:15:58.000
"Mirror"
A mirror?

00:16:03.667 --> 00:16:04.667
Klein?

00:16:16.542 --> 00:16:17.583
You okay, Kirito?

00:16:17.583 --> 00:16:18.708
Y-Yeah...

00:16:20.125 --> 00:16:21.500
Who are you?

00:16:21.500 --> 00:16:23.250
And who are you?

00:16:24.250 --> 00:16:26.833
--Who are you?
--Why did my face change?

00:16:27.333 --> 00:16:28.708
You're a guy?

00:16:28.708 --> 00:16:30.500
You were lying about being 17?

00:16:30.958 --> 00:16:32.042
That means...

00:16:32.250 --> 00:16:34.333
--You're Kirito?
--You're Klein?

00:16:35.542 --> 00:16:37.083
How?

00:16:37.083 --> 00:16:38.458
That scan...

00:16:38.458 --> 00:16:42.792
The NerveGear covers your entire head
with a high-density signaling device.

00:16:42.792 --> 00:16:45.375
So it can see what
your face looks like.

00:16:45.375 --> 00:16:47.208
But our height and body shape...

00:16:47.208 --> 00:16:51.625
When we first put on the NerveGear,
there was something called calibration...

00:16:51.625 --> 00:16:55.208
You had to touch your body
all over like this, remember?

00:16:55.208 --> 00:16:59.083
O-Oh, right... It must be
basing this on that data....

00:16:59.083 --> 00:17:01.292
But... But listen...

00:17:01.542 --> 00:17:02.500
Why?

00:17:02.500 --> 00:17:04.792
Why do all this, anyway?

00:17:05.208 --> 00:17:07.625
I'm sure he'll tell us.

00:17:07.917 --> 00:17:11.333
Right now, you must all
be wondering, "Why?"

00:17:11.333 --> 00:17:13.750
"Why would Akihiko Kayaba,

00:17:13.750 --> 00:17:18.417
developer of Sword Art Online and
the NerveGear, do such a thing?"

00:17:18.875 --> 00:17:21.750
My goal has already been achieved.

00:17:21.750 --> 00:17:24.958
I created Sword Art Online
for one reason...

00:17:24.958 --> 00:17:28.375
To create this world
and meddle in it.

00:17:29.250 --> 00:17:30.458
Kayaba...

00:17:30.458 --> 00:17:34.167
And now, all is complete.

00:17:37.250 --> 00:17:42.417
This ends the tutorial for the
official Sword Art Online launch.

00:17:43.042 --> 00:17:46.375
I wish you luck, players.

00:18:20.542 --> 00:18:24.292
<i>This is real...</i>

00:18:25.000 --> 00:18:27.292
<i>The genius who created the NerveGear</i>

00:18:27.292 --> 00:18:30.125
<i>and created a completely virtual space,</i>

00:18:30.125 --> 00:18:31.917
<i>Akihiko Kayaba.</i>

00:18:32.292 --> 00:18:35.667
<i>I admired this man, so I can tell...</i>

00:18:36.833 --> 00:18:38.250
<i>Everything he just proclaimed is true.</i>

00:18:38.250 --> 00:18:40.875
"This is a game, but it isn't something you play."
-Sword Art Online Programmer Akihiko Kayaba

00:18:40.875 --> 00:18:42.833
<i>If I die in the game,</i>

00:18:43.000 --> 00:18:45.208
<i>I will die in real life!</i>

00:18:47.333 --> 00:18:49.750
No... No!

00:18:52.917 --> 00:18:53.750
Screw you!

00:18:53.750 --> 00:18:55.458
Let me out! Let me out of here!

00:18:55.458 --> 00:18:57.625
I can't stay here... I have to
meet someone after this!

00:18:57.625 --> 00:18:58.833
What are you thinking?

00:18:58.833 --> 00:19:00.000
What are you, a thug?

00:19:02.042 --> 00:19:03.292
Let us go!

00:19:03.292 --> 00:19:04.542
Tell us you're lying!

00:19:05.500 --> 00:19:06.500
Someone!

00:19:06.500 --> 00:19:08.250
Can't anyone do something?

00:19:09.167 --> 00:19:10.750
Come with me, Klein.

00:19:13.792 --> 00:19:15.042
Listen to me.

00:19:15.042 --> 00:19:17.375
I'm heading to the
next village right now.

00:19:17.375 --> 00:19:18.792
Come with me.

00:19:20.167 --> 00:19:22.458
If everything he said is true,

00:19:22.458 --> 00:19:26.500
the only way to survive in this world is by
making yourself as strong as possible.

00:19:27.000 --> 00:19:30.250
The resources within
a virtual MMORPG,

00:19:30.542 --> 00:19:34.625
in other words, the money and
EXP we can earn, are limited.

00:19:34.958 --> 00:19:38.875
The fields surrounding the Town of Beginnings
will soon be hunted clean.

00:19:39.333 --> 00:19:43.458
To be efficient, we should set up base
in the next village right now.

00:19:43.917 --> 00:19:47.000
I know all the paths
and dangerous areas.

00:19:47.000 --> 00:19:49.583
So even at level one,
I can get there safely.

00:19:50.000 --> 00:19:52.500
But... But you know...

00:19:52.750 --> 00:19:58.875
I... stayed in line all night with friends
from another game to buy this software.

00:20:00.167 --> 00:20:03.125
They must be out there in the plaza.

00:20:03.625 --> 00:20:05.208
I can't leave them behind.

00:20:10.375 --> 00:20:12.250
<i>If it were just Klein...</i>

00:20:12.250 --> 00:20:13.417
<i>But two more...</i>

00:20:13.750 --> 00:20:15.458
<i>Or even one more...</i>

00:20:15.458 --> 00:20:16.750
Sorry.

00:20:17.167 --> 00:20:20.792
I can hardly ask you for
anything else, can I?

00:20:21.708 --> 00:20:25.125
So don't worry about it.
Go on to the next village.

00:20:26.250 --> 00:20:30.250
I used to run a guild in
my last game, you know.

00:20:30.833 --> 00:20:33.542
I can use the techniques
you taught me to get by!

00:20:34.917 --> 00:20:36.125
I see.

00:20:36.833 --> 00:20:38.917
Then let's say goodbye here.

00:20:39.250 --> 00:20:41.708
If something happens,
send me a message.

00:20:41.958 --> 00:20:43.125
Sure!

00:20:43.125 --> 00:20:45.375
Okay. See you around, Klein.

00:20:45.375 --> 00:20:46.750
Kirito!

00:20:52.417 --> 00:20:53.500
Hey...

00:20:53.833 --> 00:20:55.167
Kirito.

00:20:55.167 --> 00:20:59.167
The real you is actually
kinda cute, huh?

00:21:00.083 --> 00:21:02.125
I like you better this way.

00:21:04.042 --> 00:21:08.042
And that unkempt face of yours
suits you 10 times better.

00:21:41.417 --> 00:21:44.542
<i>I'm... I'm...</i>

00:21:44.792 --> 00:21:46.792
<i>I'm going to survive...</i>

00:21:50.875 --> 00:21:52.792
<i>In this world!</i>

00:22:09.458 --> 00:22:13.875
<i>Mitometeta okubyou na kako</i>
<i>The cowardly past that I'd acknowledged</i>

00:22:14.208 --> 00:22:19.667
<i>Wakaranai mama ni</i>
<i>Still not understanding why,</i>

00:22:20.000 --> 00:22:30.542
<i>I stand behind myself, scared</i>
<i>Projecting reality onto today</i>

00:22:30.875 --> 00:22:35.875
<i>I've drawn so many skies</i>

00:22:36.208 --> 00:22:40.542
<i>This must be my fleeting heart</i>

00:22:40.875 --> 00:22:43.250
<i>Out of control</i>

00:22:43.583 --> 00:22:48.875
<i>In my dreams, this body soars so high</i>

00:22:49.292 --> 00:22:54.125
<i>And it can brush away any fears that cling to me</i>

00:22:54.458 --> 00:23:00.583
<i>Asleep inside me, these budding</i>
<i>feelings start to expand</i>

00:23:00.917 --> 00:23:04.542
<i>I realize this, weak as I am...</i>
<i>As long as I had you</i>

00:23:04.875 --> 00:23:09.833
<i>I could stay strong in this dark world</i>

00:23:10.167 --> 00:23:15.833
<i>My heart will dream a long dream forever</i>

00:23:16.750 --> 00:23:19.208
<i>I want to always be with you</i>

00:23:19.542 --> 00:23:24.875
<i>I'll give you everything I have...</i>

00:23:35.875 --> 00:23:39.083
"In the game's first month, 2,000 died"

00:23:41.042 --> 00:23:44.542
"Floor 1 has yet to be cleared--
December 2, 2022"

00:23:47.042 --> 00:23:53.152
Next Time: "Beater."
